message:
Add random, brand-specific swatch & gradient fetching to UnityBrandColorSceme;
Refactor all previous HexToColor calls to use the U.Material function;
Move UnityBrandColorScheme into Utilities

Add support for UnityBrandColorScheme gradient refactor to MainMenu;
Remove material instancing errors occurring in MainMenu, use GetMaterialClone;
Refine Animation timing in SnapToFace function

Refactor menu to support creation on both left and right devices;
Add ILockableRay; Add support for locking/unlocking the default ray,
and additional default proxy ray state handling, allowing for devices like the
menu to prevent Blink from re-enabling the defaultRay;
Separate VRMenuItemAttribute into separate class

Add additional functionality to core Actions;
Move Actions from /scripts/Actions into /Actions, they now have suporting files, icons;
Create Icons & Scripts folders within /Actions

Move menuOrigin & menuInputOrigin into new IMenuOrigins interface, from IMainMenu;
Derive IMainMenu from IMenuOrigins;
(menu origins will be used in SelectTool's radial menu)

Fix FlagsPropertyDrawer so that there is only one possible value for every combination of flags;
Create U.UI and add new FilteredMaskField function for above fix;
Move DoubleClick and IsDirectEvent/IsValidEvent to U.UI;
Add RaySlider (same as RayButton, but for Slider);

Prevent the main menu from being triggered by the left thumbstick button;
Clicking the UnityIcon button hovering around the controller opens the main menu;
For now it is on action3, but should be removed completely in favor of UnityIcon button

Implement actions in EditorVR; SpawnActions() sets up actions;
Remove Polling for ShowMenu input, MainMenu is shown/hidden via the Menu Activator button;
Add menu hiding support in SpawnDefaultTools();
Add transform tool functionality hookup in ConnectInterfaces

Add support for EVR's handling of Toggles; EVR creates a collection of Toggles;
Adds new toggles to the collection as Tools are spawned in SpawnTool();
Removes toggles from the collection in DespawnTool();
Sets the toggle collection in each object implementing IUsesToggles;

Fix issue with PixelRaycastModule.UpdateRaycast caused by early-out reafactor;
Remove UIActions workaround from MultiplRayInputModule. Instead, we now deactivate
the original rayorigin while draging with fake rays.

Update prefabs for new masking; Update CuboidLayout to use absolute value for size;
Add a Setup to InspectorListViewItem to trigger a resize and properly position cubes;
Update SetMaterials to remove custom materials from mask graphics

Add support for hiding/showing the cone in the DefaultProxyRay;
Remove unused coroutine field;
The cone should be hidden when the default proxy ray is hidden (showing main menu, etc)

Add front resize-icons forward offset based on workspace angle in WorkspaceBase,
compensating for the blendshape'd  mesh covering the icons when rotated vertically;
Clean up formatting as well

Setup/refine min bounds and dynamic face adjustment values for all workspaces;
Add support for blocking front/back resizing of minimal workspaces (console/profiler);
Remove workspacePanelsVisible

Remove need for Workspace UI to drive handle positions and scales;
Workspace resize handles are now placed under the top face container,
resizing themselves accordingly without manual control

Fix errors and warnings in HapticsModule caused by not having Oculus Utilities

First fix is to wrap LateUpdate in #if ENABLE_OVR_INPUT to remove call to missing OVRHaptics class;
Second fix is to leave the usage of m_MasterIntensity in Pulse in order to eliminate assigned but never used warning.

Refactor Manipulator-specific code out of the Handle classes, and into BaseManipulator;
Add ResetDirectSelectionState to IUsesDirectSelection to show manipulator on ray select after direct select;
Add scale bump to radial handle; Make handle tips face the direction of movement

Fix a bug where moving objects in/out of miniworlds would cause previously manipulated objects to move;
Fix workspaces showing up in miniworld (UI layer and frame collider);
Fix a bug where objects coming out of miniworlds would pop for a frame

Finish mesh grouping changes; Misc fixes to Annotation tool;
Fix ILinkedObjects to remove objects and lists as they are disconnected;
Fix issue with color picker where edge selections would be transparent

Remove GC from use of AnimateProperty and switch to version in TransitionUtils;
Remove GC from use of AnimateProperty in ProxyNode;
Remove GC from GetDeviceType

Add an editor window for editing/viewing serialized feedback info (i.e. presentation counts);
Refactor SerializedPreferenceModule to support access while EXR is not running;
Fix issue where Feedback preferences can get overwritten with blank data

Renamed and set up Mouse action map;
Use ICustomActionMap in MouseMovementTool
Instantiate material in Ring.cs

Clean up Ring prefab;
Modify core fadeout behavior;
Reposition ring UI on scroll wheel

Fix CompilationTest if checked out to a folder called EditorXR;
Remove build tests (will be done by CloudBuild);
Fix build errors caused by Ring.cs

Fix tests;
Rename EditorVRContext to EditorXRContext;
Put MoveWorkspacesTool in a namespace;
Disable context switcher UI in VRView--switching contexts currently breaks rays

Add a delay to floor indicator;
Update variable names in PlayerFloor for consistency;
Add FloorBorder texture with arrow in front;
Update PlayerFloor materials to not render on top;
Rename LocomotionTool assets for clarity

Disable spatial UI animator between transitions to fix fade-out bug;
Early-out in OnAutoOpenStateChanged if playing or entering play mode, and remove setting XR enabled on Awake;
Revert changes to SpatialMenu.prefab

Fix SpatialMenu.prefab in 2017.4;
Rename prefab fields to work properly in 2018.1 and below;
Find-replace all on:
-  m_SourcePrefab -> m_ParentPrefab
-  m_IsPrefabAsset -> m_IsPrefabParent
-  m_CorrespondingSourceObject -> m_PrefabParentObject

Remove TextMeshPro optional dependency code to fix builds;
This code is obsolete as TextMeshPro is a requirement, and other code already caused compile errors if TextMeshPro was missing from the project;
Encapsulate usages of OptionalDependencyAttribute with #if UNITY_EDITOR to fix builds;
Encapsulate usages of RequireTag with #if UNITY_EDITOR
Refactor CreateGameObjectWithComponent to avoid inconsistent usage of component local variable;
Clean up warnings in VRSmoothCamera that occur during builds

Remove MonoBehavior parent class from modules that dont need it;

Call InitializeInputManager in DeviceInputModule.LoadModule to prevent multiple input managers from begin added to the scene;
Disable EditorVR on Awake to wait until VRView is opened;
Add ModuleLoadOrders to avoid issues when loading modules;
Manually call Initialize on ViewerModule and MenuModule to fix setup issues

Change initialization order to get trackedObjectInput set up correctly;
Explicitly initialize selected modules in EditorVR on opening VRView;
Move module load code that creates new gameobjects to Initialize;
Add null checks to prevent exception

Update initialization code and fix issues caused by new deserialization sequence;
Fix issues where modules retain state between runs of EditorXR, or cleared state in the wrong place;
Start/stop RunInEditMode on all modules in the EditorXR assembly when starting and stopping EditorXR;
Close VRView when unloading EditorVR module;
Call DisconnectInterfaces on tools when we shut down EditorXR so that we don't leak serializers;
Remove HideFlags from VRView;
Fix issues where serialized prefab references were being overwritten by instances on creation;
Delay loading serialized workspaces until proxies become active

Group remaining EXR objects under module parent;
Remove EditorVR module dependencies that exist only for updates;
Set up behavior callback orders;
Switch to using EditorVR to call behavior callback methods to fix crash on recompile;
Put FeedbackModule in Modules namespace;
Make tooltipcanvas a child of EditorVR to make sure it is ignored;
Fix info spam in CameraUtils.LocalRotateTowardCamera

Move Behavior callbacks to EditingContextManager;
Move EditorVR setup and shutdown out of OnEnable and OnDisable;
Move SetRunInEdit code out of EditorVR and into EditingContextManager

Convert IControlSpatialHinting to IProvides/UsesSpatialHinting;
Move Node into Interfaces assembly for reference therein;
Fix naming of m_ToolsMenuButtonTemplate

Convert IControlHaptics to IProvides/UsesControlHaptics;
Move HapticPulse to interfaces assembly for access therein;
Fix haptics by setting up HapticsModule in Initialize

Hook up touch events in MultipleRayInputModule;
Make SnappingModule and groundSnapping property public for setting in CompanionModule;
Add Selection.set_activeTransform;
Rename Tests/Editor/Unity.Labs.EditorXR.asmdef to Tests/Editor/Unity.Labs.EditorXR.EditorTests.asmdef to avoid confusion

Clean up MultipleRayInputModule;

Introduce RayInputModule to break up MRIM;
Revert changes to handles related to handling null eventData.rayOrigin

Move version check into its own file in the CCU assembly;
Split asmdef patch into PolyToolkit and SpatialTracking;
Update readme to reflect current setup process;
Add stub class with serialized fields to ensure EditorVR default references survive package import

Fix package validation warnings;
Update package files to latest state of package starter kit;
Move CompilationTest to utils package

Remove VRLineRenderer;

Update references to VRLineRenderer;
Update missing XML comments

Rename EditorXREvents to EditorXRAnalyticsEvents;
Remove unused usings;
Misc cleanup

Remove redundant <para> from XML comments;
Fix null reference exception in AdaptivePositionModule that can occur if no MainCamera exists;
Bump version number and dependency version numbers

Fix blink visuals;
Fix issue where multiple settings menu providers stack up due to missing rayOrigin argument in DisconnectInterfaces;
Remove Tuple backfill and use built-in Tuple as dictionary key since KeyValuePair is not equatable;
Bump version number;
Update CHANGELOG.md
